{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoManager"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EditorUndoRedoManager"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoManager"},{"type":"text","text":" is a manager for "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo"},{"type":"text","text":" objects associated with edited scenes. Each scene has its own undo history and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoManager"},{"text":" ensures that each action performed in the editor gets associated with a proper scene. For actions not related to scenes (","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProjectSettings","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" edits, external resources, etc.), a separate global history is used."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The usage is mostly the same as "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". You create and commit actions and the manager automatically decides under-the-hood what scenes it belongs to. The scene is deduced based on the first operation in an action, using the object from the operation. The rules are as follows:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"text":", use the currently edited scene;","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is a built-in resource, use the scene from its path;"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is external resource or anything else, use global history."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This guessing can sometimes yield false results, so you can provide a custom context object when creating an action.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoManager"},{"text":" is intended to be used by Godot editor plugins. You can obtain it using ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorPlugin\/getUndoRedo()"},{"text":". For non-editor uses or plugins that don’t need to integrate with the editor’s undo history, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo","isActive":true},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The manager’s API is mostly the same as in ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo"},{"text":", so you can refer to its documentation for more examples. The main difference is that ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoManager","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" uses object + method name for actions, instead of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Callable"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent